Nowadays, users can move, deposit and withdraw the resources of network wantonly. That is due to the wireless network which is flourishing, and the hold-device which is more and more popular. The traditional net is lack of considering user's moving states and information. So it will cause a lot of loopholes and incidents of security. In this paper, we propose a security management scheme for heterogeneous wireless networks, and can be adjusted by according to the difference of the user's moving state. Therefore, the policy can react the moving change of users promptly to achieve the goal of guaranteed safeness.